Description: Implements a Bayesian quantile regression approach using the Expectation-Maximization (EM) algorithm 
    and several MCMC methods with observation weights. Includes fast C++ implementations using Rcpp, RcppEigen, 
    and RcppArmadillo for linear algebra, and Boost (via the BH package) for special functions such as Bessel. 
    The package also calls 'GIGrvg' for sampling from Generalized Inverse Gaussian distributions.
